name: "Flying Fish" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Colored pencil, brush pen, liner pen, and felt pen on reclaimed cardboard with some digital color embellishment.] I floated on the magical boat thru the dangerous rocks and tides, and the sky melted into millions of colors. Lights blinding and absurd flashed through the misty air, and flying fish (perhaps disembodied, perhaps not) arched through the ether spreading fear and happiness... What a nice way to spend an eternity... ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
